         <abstract>
            <p>In this paper we describe two classes of simultaneous Pell equations of the form x&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - dy&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = z&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - ey&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 1 with no solutions in positive integers x, y, z. The proof is elementary and covers the case (d, e) = (8, 5), which was solved by E. Brown using very deep methods.</p>
          </abstract>
